text: The banded mud moray (Gymnothorax chlamydatus) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the western Pacific Ocean.Gymnothorax chlamydatus at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Snyder in 1908, because of dark bands along its body.Common names for Gymnothorax chlamydatus at www.fishbase.org. ==References== ==External links== * chlamydatus Category:Fish of Oceania Category:Fish of the Pacific Ocean Category:Fish described in 1908
